    audiobook: true,
    physicalbook: false,
    review: 'In "Talking as Fast a I Can", Lauren Graham shares stories about her life growing up, becoming an actress and living in Hollywood. She plays the iconic "Lorelai Gilmore" in the TV-series "Gilmore Girls" which aired for seven seasons between 2000-2007. I was late to the party and watched the show for the first time in 2017. I became obsessively in love with everything about it, and have re-watched the show several times in just a few years. I guess I was in desperate need of something to fill the big Stars-Hollow shaped hole in my life. Unfortunately wasn\'t this book enough to do so. Lauren Graham seems like a wonderful woman, but I couldn\'t help but wanting her to be Lorelai Gilmore instead. Although I enjoyed her reflections on Gilmore Girls and on being Lorelai Gilmore, it was not enough to make this an amazing book. I would easily listen to her for hours telling how it was to do each an every episode, so maybe this book would never contain enough details to make me happy. I\'m glad I read it (I even finished it in 2 days), and I really couldn\'t not read it given how much I love Gilmore Girls.',
